Load the Data

# load data
anes <- read.csv("data/anes-2012-therms.csv")
ccap <- read.csv("data/ccap2012.csv")
gay <- read.csv("data/gayreshaped.csv")

# subset lacour and green's data into study 1 and study 2
gay1 <- subset(gay, study == 1)
gay2 <- subset(gay, study == 2)

Anomaly 1

# 2x2 matrix of histograms
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# histograms of the gay feeling thermometers
hist(ccap$gaytherm, breaks = 50)
hist(gay1$therm1, breaks = 50)
hist(gay2$therm1, breaks = 50)
hist(anes$ft_gay, breaks = 50)

Anomaly 1

# 2x4 matrix of qq-plots
par(mfrow = c(2, 3))

# qq-plots of the gay feeling thermometers
qqplot(ccap$gaytherm, anes$ft_gay); abline(0, 1)
qqplot(ccap$gaytherm, gay1$therm1); abline(0, 1)
qqplot(ccap$gaytherm, gay2$therm1); abline(0, 1)
qqplot(anes$ft_gay, gay1$therm1); abline(0, 1)
qqplot(anes$ft_gay, gay2$therm1); abline(0, 1)
qqplot(gay1$therm1, gay2$therm1); abline(0, 1)

Anomaly 2

# 2x2 matrix of histograms
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# plot pre- and post-election ft ratings for each candidate
plot(anes$ft_barack_obama_pre, anes$ft_barack_obama_post)
plot(anes$ft_mitt_romney_pre, anes$ft_mitt_romney_post)
plot(anes$ft_joe_biden_pre, anes$ft_joe_biden_post)
plot(anes$ft_paul_ryan_pre, anes$ft_paul_ryan_post)

Anomaly 2

# 2x2 matrix of histograms
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# plot the feeling thermometers for wave 1 and wave 2 in the control group for study 1 and study 2
gay2_control <- subset(gay2, treatment == "No Contact")
plot(gay2_control$therm1, gay2_control$therm2)
plot(gay2_control$therm1, gay2_control$therm3)
plot(gay2_control$therm1, gay2_control$therm4)

Anomaly 3

# 2x2 matrix of histograms
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# create histograms of the differences between the politician feeling thermometers in the pre and post
hist(anes$ft_barack_obama_pre - anes$ft_barack_obama_post, breaks = 75, xlim = c(-100, 100))
hist(anes$ft_mitt_romney_pre - anes$ft_mitt_romney_post, breaks = 75, xlim = c(-100, 100))
hist(anes$ft_joe_biden_pre - anes$ft_joe_biden_post, breaks = 75, xlim = c(-100, 100))
hist(anes$ft_paul_ryan_pre - anes$ft_paul_ryan_post, breaks = 75, xlim = c(-100, 100))

Anomaly 3

# 2x2 matrix of histograms
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))

# create histograms of the differences between the waves of study 2
hist(gay2_control$therm1 - gay2_control$therm2, breaks = 25, xlim = c(-100, 100))
hist(gay2_control$therm1 - gay2_control$therm3, breaks = 25, xlim = c(-100, 100))
hist(gay2_control$therm1 - gay2_control$therm4, breaks = 25, xlim = c(-100, 100))
